Architecture & Audit Readiness

Agent Flow Architecture:
The autonomous agent system is modular, with each agent responsible for a distinct workflow segment. Agents communicate via secure APIs and log every action with timestamps and input/output snapshots.

Components:
- Input Handler: Parses structured/unstructured data from GCS buckets and user uploads.
- Agent Core: Executes task logic, invokes sub-agents, and handles exceptions.
- Audit Logger: Captures every action with metadata, enabling traceability and compliance.
- Output Formatter: Generates annotated tables, diagrams, and onboarding-ready documents.

